<subSubSection id="275A50FF166B9E85A2B884A37C656416" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="1B93E6500C4CE9454DD639A97DF68841" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6A2A45A471B86B9B65B1D29AE4C52B39" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
The name of the genus is based on the geographic distribution of its five species, all of which occur in Africa and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="A51DFB5C84BC9592BA82A324AF6F5F23" authorityName="D.L.Szlachetko, J.Mytnik-Ejsmont &amp; E.Grochocka" authorityYear="2013" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pectinariella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pectinariella" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="25A65E8380DBF48202E4C6F80966291D" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Pectinariella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which they were previously placed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D99AC7E0F1AAE5825EBCEDAF40DF49A8" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="30635C6D3676471670B1FD645C0FA86B" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="15A1BF054A0DC74216284ABBCC0B01F3" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName id="A403B257ADEE6546445E2B26479573A6" authority="M.Simo &amp; Stevart, 2018" authorityName="M. Simo &amp; Stevart" authorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Afropectinariella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Afropectinariella" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AEFA405F519D119F6F02DABD0D7D1849" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Afropectinariella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles the related genera 
<taxonomicName id="AECAC5608B4253394493B9E3909C7CF9" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Dolabrifolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolabrifolia" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E790996EB796BE585DA3CF7E55E2A90A" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Dolabrifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E9C51678EFCB417005D3E7E26BEC5C0B" authorityName="D.L.Szlachetko, J.Mytnik-Ejsmont &amp; E.Grochocka" authorityYear="2013" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pectinariella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pectinariella" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DA01FBA7CFEB0737372C3C9446C7505B" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Pectinariella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a sessile ovary, i.e. without a pedicel and with a very short peduncle that is hardly developed, but differs from 
<taxonomicName id="5B18B907D1478602DED9F845D0980334" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Dolabrifolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolabrifolia" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="691C22ABC525FF9B421FC051588B1257" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Dolabrifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its elongate leaves that are never compressed laterally (vs. imbricate and laterally compressed) and from 
<taxonomicName id="7052360CF8A9969632C7BA84664C4234" authorityName="D.L.Szlachetko, J.Mytnik-Ejsmont &amp; E.Grochocka" authorityYear="2013" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pectinariella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pectinariella" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F37674D0DB720B3DD45F0D8940EC43F0" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Pectinariella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its transversely oval lip that is wider than long (vs. the lip longer that wide) and its occurrence in continental Africa and Gulf of Guinea islands (vs. Madagascar and adjacent islands).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C78A46D236621C568F471FD16BE45CA8" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph id="9B20606D40ED10C3FBEAFE40799524EB" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9BF2BF485AA372F993BD23EBF2F271E6" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Epiphytic herbs. Stem erect to pendent, branched and loosely leafy. Leaves fleshy, alternate and elongate, subulate or linear to oblong-ovate, apex acute to apiculate, petiole twisted. Inflorescences suberect and subsessile, in general 1-flowered, sometimes 2-flowered, borne along the stem or opposite a leaf, sheath brown. Flowers small, nearly sessile in the axils of the leaves, white and often scented. Floral bract one, amplexicaul, broadly ovate. Sepals and petals elliptic to obovate, apex subacute. Lip entire, ovate-triangular, ecallose, apex acute to apiculate. Spur ellipsoid or subcylindric, straight or slightly curved, sometimes hooked, with a wide mouth at the base of the lip, apex acute, often blunt or swollen in the apical half. Peduncle short, hardly developed. Pollinia 2, pyriform, often sessile on one or two viscidia, without a distinct stipe or shortly stipitate, rarely with a well-developed stipe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CCB40AE21ED6A77D9322458618D5ECEF" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName id="55A26CE84260B9BC4AE3C9BD32B1DBE7" authority="M.Simo &amp; Stevart, 2018" authorityName="M. Simo &amp; Stevart" authorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Afropectinariella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Afropectinariella" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A78119A8107E46B03AB6F76B440F63D6" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Afropectinariella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes five species from continental Africa and the Gulf of Guinea Islands, one of which is endemic to 
<normalizedToken id="0E9CF1D06B4A0F702D4580655B69F40C" originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="B6D343F3714759D3400583624EAEBB72" originalValue="Tomé">Tome</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="5208BCDF4896B96F6DE8A009475535A0" originalValue="Príncipe">Principe</normalizedToken>
Islands. Four of these five species were placed in 
<taxonomicName id="A6E2155A0610871DB4B05A1578A8B147" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Angraecum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Angraecum subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="section" section="Pectinaria" species="doratophyllum" subSpecies="sect.">Angraecum sect. Pectinaria</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="283D51206C8EB8F0CE7DF552EB83E1D0" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4108894" author="Garay, LA" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" refId="B7" refString="Garay, LA, 1973. Systematics of the genus Angraecum (Orchidaceae). Kew Bulletin 28: 495-516. https://doi.org/10.2307/4108894" title="Systematics of the genus Angraecum (Orchidaceae). Kew Bulletin 28: 495 - 516." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4108894" year="1973">Garay (1973)</bibRefCitation>
and, more recently, in 
<taxonomicName id="E612F6E51333D57DCB2B20D79711C218" authorityName="D.L.Szlachetko, J.Mytnik-Ejsmont &amp; E.Grochocka" authorityYear="2013" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pectinariella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pectinariella" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BC929166BC83DCD327D76C758F442EF8" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Pectinariella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as originally circumscribed by 
<bibRefCitation id="44BD9E2D841F9D93BE211E564DA100B2" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2478/biorc-2013-0004" author="Szlachetko, DL" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" refId="B25" refString="Szlachetko, DL, Tukallo, P, Mytnik-Ejsmont, J, Grochocka, E, 2013. Reclassification of the Angraecum-alliance (Orchidaceae, Vandoideae) based on molecular and morphological data. Biodiversity Research and Conservation 29: 1-23. https://doi.org/10.2478/biorc-2013-0004" title="Reclassification of the Angraecum-alliance (Orchidaceae, Vandoideae) based on molecular and morphological data. Biodiversity Research and Conservation 29: 1 - 23." url="https://doi.org/10.2478/biorc-2013-0004" year="2013">Szlachetko et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. A detailed taxonomic treatment of these five species is presented in 
<bibRefCitation id="6B77D2386E590FA773CA04ED168CD67D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364414X682184" author="Simo-Droissart, M" journalOrPublisher="Paul Parey, Berlin" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" refId="B17" refString="Simo-Droissart, M, Sonke, B, Droissart, V, Geerinck, D, Micheneau, C, Lowry, II PP, Plunkett, GM, Hardy, OJ, Stevart, T, 2014. Taxonomic revision of the continental African species of Angraecum section Pectinaria (Orchidaceae). Systematic Botany 39: 725-739. https://doi.org/10.1600/036364414X682184" title="Taxonomic revision of the continental African species of Angraecum section Pectinaria (Orchidaceae). Systematic Botany 39: 725 - 739." url="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364414X682184" year="2014">Simo-Droissart et al. (2014)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
